<h2><a name='sect0' href='#toc0'>Name</a></h2>
<p>
PRTE_FILEM - PRTE MCA File Management (FileM) Framework: Overview
of PRTE[cq]s FileM framework, and selected modules.
<h2><a name='sect1' href='#toc1'>Description</a></h2>
<p>
FileM is
a utility framework used by PRTE for a variety of purposes, including the
transport of checkpoint files, preloading user binaries, and preloading
of user files.
<h2><a name='sect2' href='#toc2'>Available Components</a></h2>
<p>
PRTE currently ships with one FileM component:
C]rshR]. <p>
The following MCA parameters apply to all components:
<dl>

<dt>B]CB]filem_base_verboseB]R]
</dt>
<dd>Set the verbosity level for all components. Default is 0, or silent except
on error. </dd>
</dl>

<h3><a name='sect3' href='#toc3'>rsh FileM Component</a></h3>
<p>
The C]rshR] component uses C]rcpR] or C]scpR]
to do its file transfers. This component requires the use of passwordless
C]rshR] or C]sshR] between all nodes. <p>
The C]rshR] component has the following
MCA parameters:
<dl>

<dt>B]CB]filem_rsh_priorityB]R] </dt>
<dd>The component[cq]s priority
to use when selecting the most appropriate component for a run. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]filem_rsh_verboseB]R]
</dt>
<dd>Set the verbosity level for this component. Default is 0, or silent except
on error. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]filem_rsh_rcpB]R] </dt>
<dd>The program to use to copy files. Generally
will be C]rcpR] or C]scpR]. </dd>

<dt>B]CB]filem_rsh_rshB]R] </dt>
<dd>The program used to remotely
log into a given machine and remove files. Generally will be C]rshR] or
C]sshR]. </dd>
</dl>

<h3><a name='sect4' href='#toc4'>none FileM Component</a></h3>
<p>
The C]noneR] component simply selects no FileM
component. All of the FileM function calls return immediately with PRTE_SUCCESS.
<p>
This component is the last component to be selected by default. This means
that if another component is available, and the C]noneR] component was
not explicity requested then PRTE will attempt to activate all of the available
components before falling back to this component.
